.SS 0. RUN_COMMAND
.P
\fBMESSAGE\fR
.br
Parses and runs the payload as sway commands
.P
\fBREPLY\fR
.br
An array of objects corresponding to each command that was parsed.\& Each object
has the property \fIsuccess\fR, which is a boolean indicating whether the command
was successful.\& The object may also contain the properties \fIerror\fR and \fIparse_error\fR.\&
The \fIerror\fR property is a human readable error message while \fIparse_error\fR is a
boolean indicating whether the reason the command failed was because the command
was unknown or not able to be parsed.\&
.P
\fBExample Reply:\fR
.nf
.RS 4
[
	{
		"success": true
	},
	{
		"success": false,
		"parse_error": true,
		"error": "Invalid/unknown command"
	}
]
.fi
.RE
